Good catch! I'd suggest moving up `get_internals_ptr()` to mirror the code from `detail:: get_internals()`. This is invariant with respect to `Py_Finalize()`:

```c++
auto *&internals_ptr = detail::get_internals_ptr();
if (builtins.contains(id) && isinstance<capsule>(builtins[id]))
    internals_ptr = *static_cast<internals **>(capsule(builtins[id]));

Py_Finalize();

delete internals_ptr;
internals_ptr = nullptr;
```

*Maybe* easier to read if you do something like
```
if len(vhost.addrs) == 0:
